** CVSsuck - inefficient cvs repository grabber via cvs client/server protocol **

usage:

% cvssuck [-s] [-t] [-o output-directory] cvsroot module

-s : skeleton mode
-t : translation mode

example:

(0) Setup .cvspass for the repository

% cvs -d :pserver:anonymous@cvs.m17n.org:/cvs/cvs login
(Logging in to anonymous@cvs.m17n.org)
CVS password: 

(1) Grab the repository

% cvssuck $HOME/.cvsroot/cvssuck :pserver:anonymous@cvs.m17n.org:/cvs/cvs cvssuck

requirement:

  ruby-1.4.6	http://www.ruby-lang.org/
  cvs-1.10	http://www.cvshome.org/
  rcs-5.7	ftp://ftp.cs.purdue.edu/pub/RCS/

author:
  Tanaka Akira <akr@m17n.org>
